Amazon API Gateway is a fully managed service that helps you create, publish, secure, and monitor APIs for your backend applications (like Node.js, Lambda, etc).
Think of it as a “front door” for your application —
All client requests (web, mobile, etc.) go through API Gateway before reaching your backend service

Purpose	Description
Routing	Sends HTTP requests to the right backend (like AWS Lambda, EC2, or any REST endpoint).
Security	Supports authentication (JWT, Cognito, IAM) and rate-limiting (throttling).
Transformation	Can modify requests/responses (headers, body) before sending to backend.
Monitoring	Works with CloudWatch to log metrics and errors.
Scalability	Automatically scales to handle millions of requests per second.


